  "answer": "# Summary\n\nBased on the available failure modes for Chiller 6, when the Liquid Refrigerant Evaporator Temperature drops, the most likely failure is **Evaporator Water side fouling**.\n\nA drop in evaporator temperature typically indicates reduced heat transfer efficiency in the evaporator, which is a characteristic symptom of water-side fouling. Fouling (accumulation of deposits, scale, or biological growth) on the water side of the evaporator reduces the heat exchange capability, causing the refrigerant temperature to drop as less heat is being absorbed from the chilled water circuit.",
